</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA91118E3AFFD9FF6AFB38708EFAED" blockId="6.[151,1127,1133,1392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">
<emphasis id="B9614D038E3AFFD9FF6AFB387071FACB" bold="true" box="[151,339,1267,1286]" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">Original description.</emphasis>
‘C. rufescens, thorace punctis duobus, elytris numerosis cyaneo nigris, clypeo integro.Habitat in nova Hollandia. Dom. 
<collectingRegion id="49D15FF38E3AFFD9FE8DFAC6708AFAED" box="[368,424,1293,1312]" country="Gambia" name="North Bank" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">Banks</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA91118E3AFFD9FF48FAE37046FABD" blockId="6.[151,1127,1133,1392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">
Statura nostratum. Antennae apice nigrae. Clypeus rotundatus, integer, rufus, punctis duobus nigris in medio, elytra rufa, punctis circiter novem lateralibus majoribus nigro cyaneis. Margo subtus fasciis tribus. Corpus flavescens.’ (
<bibRefCitation id="EF84ECE08E3AFFD9FF2EFA96707BFABD" author="FABRICIUS J. C." bookContentInfo="(14) + 832 pp." box="[211,345,1373,1392]" firstAuthor="FABRICIUS" journalOrPublisher="O? cina Libraria Kortii, Flensburgi et Lipsiae" pageId="6" pageNumber="663" refId="ref18820" refString="FABRICIUS J. C. 1775: Systema entomologiae, sistens insectorvm classes, ordines, genera, species, adiectis synonymis, locis, descriptionibvs, observationibvs. O? cina Libraria Kortii, Flensburgi et Lipsiae, (14) + 832 pp." title="Systema entomologiae, sistens insectorvm classes, ordines, genera, species, adiectis synonymis, locis, descriptionibvs, observationibvs" type="book" year="1775">FABRICIUS 1775</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA91118E3AFFD9FF6AFA427281FA6D" blockId="6.[151,1127,1417,1632]" box="[151,931,1417,1440]" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">
<emphasis id="B9614D038E3AFFD9FF6AFA427066FA6D" bold="true" box="[151,324,1417,1440]" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">Current status.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C15EA928E3AFFD9FEB6FA4272BDFA6D" authority="(Fabricius, 1775)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[331,927,1417,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aspidimorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deusta" subGenus="Aspidimorpha">
<emphasis id="B9614D038E3AFFD9FEB6FA4270C0FA6D" box="[331,482,1417,1440]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">Aspidimorpha</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B9614D038E3AFFD9FE0CFA4273AAFA6D" box="[497,648,1417,1440]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">Aspidimorpha</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B9614D038E3AFFD9FD65FA4273FCFA6D" box="[664,734,1417,1440]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">deusta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF84ECE08E3AFFD9FD11FA4272B5FA6D" author="FABRICIUS J. C." bookContentInfo="(14) + 832 pp." box="[748,919,1417,1440]" firstAuthor="Fabricius" journalOrPublisher="O? cina Libraria Kortii, Flensburgi et Lipsiae" pageId="6" pageNumber="663" refId="ref18820" refString="FABRICIUS J. C. 1775: Systema entomologiae, sistens insectorvm classes, ordines, genera, species, adiectis synonymis, locis, descriptionibvs, observationibvs. O? cina Libraria Kortii, Flensburgi et Lipsiae, (14) + 832 pp." title="Systema entomologiae, sistens insectorvm classes, ordines, genera, species, adiectis synonymis, locis, descriptionibvs, observationibvs" type="book" year="1775">Fabricius, 1775</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA91118E3AFFD9FF6AFA627255F9AD" blockId="6.[151,1127,1417,1632]" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">
<emphasis id="B9614D038E3AFFD9FF6AFA627025FA0D" bold="true" box="[151,263,1449,1472]" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C15EA928E3AFFD9FEECFA627098FA0D" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[273,442,1449,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cassida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deusta">
<emphasis id="B9614D038E3AFFD9FEECFA627098FA0D" box="[273,442,1449,1472]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">Cassida deusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the 
<collectingRegion id="49D15FF38E3AFFD9FD29FA627235FA0D" box="[724,791,1449,1472]" country="Gambia" name="North Bank" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">Banks</collectingRegion>
collection and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF84ECE08E3AFFD9FC34FA627544FA0D" author="ZIMSEN E." bookContentInfo="656 pp." box="[969,1126,1449,1472]" firstAuthor="ZIMSEN" journalOrPublisher="Munksgaard, Copenhagen" pageId="6" pageNumber="663" refId="ref19364" refString="ZIMSEN E. 1964: The type material of I. C. Fabricius. Munksgaard, Copenhagen, 656 pp." title="The type material of I. C. Fabricius" type="book" year="1964">ZIMSEN (1964)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<specimenCount id="9D135A988E3AFFD9FF05FA0270B4FA2D" box="[248,406,1481,1504]" pageId="6" pageNumber="663" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
in BMNH and one in JFUK. This is the only case when the JFUK specimen agrees morphologically with those in BMNH and is also pinned on the same kind of pin: therefore all three can probably be regarded as 
<typeStatus id="54AE2FB38E3AFFD9FD2BF9C27215F9ED" box="[726,823,1545,1568]" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">syntypes</typeStatus>
. The taxon is clearly distinct morphologically from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C15EA928E3AFFD9FE3AF9E27390F98D" box="[455,690,1577,1600]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aspidimorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="663" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9614D038E3AFFD9FE3AF9E2737CF98D" box="[455,606,1577,1600]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">Aspidimorpha</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
and the name has been correctly applied since its description thus there is no need for a 
<typeStatus id="54AE2FB38E3AFFD9FD71F98273CCF9AD" box="[652,750,1609,1632]" pageId="6" pageNumber="663">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
